2:31pm
CrossFit Total today.  Numbers weren’t great. Tried for 405 dead but missed it. 405 used to be pretty routine for me, but haven’t hit that in a while. Sweatshirt by @jerseypitsrescue courtesy of @karianneanthes. @crossfittraining #crossfit #crossfittraining

9:36am
Nice brisk morning for a run at @crossfitranch. Haven’t done much regular running this year, some rucking and a lot of CrossFit.  Run felt good.  #crossfit #crossfittraining @crossfittraining

2:12pm
I am so bad at handstand push-ups that @dougthedogo decided to get involved. This was the second round of 3 rounds of run 400 10 hspu. I did the first round unbroken and was hoping to do the same here. But she messed me up causing me to miss rep 8. #dogoargentino #crossfit #crossfittraining @crossfittraining #hspu

10:37am
Sore from cindy yesterday so I did a quick workout that didn’t put a huge demand on sore areas. 50-double unders 10 hang power cleans at 115, 40-8, 30-6, 20-4, 10-2. @crossfittraining #crossfit #crossfittraining
6am class this morning at @crossfitfortius  Had I know they were going to do ‘cindy’, I wouldn’t have gone. #crossfit #crossfittraining @crossfittraining #supportyourlocalbox
Christmas gift idea. A knife from @specoperator and his company @halffaceblades. Check them out. Former fellow navy guy. #knife #halffaceblades

People often comment about the poster I have hanging of ‘The Rock’. The summer I graduated from high school I saw it in the movie theater and it changed the course of my life. A few months later I would drop out of college and enlist. All because I walked out of the theater thinking... “I wonder if I have what it takes to be a.......”. (And i wasn’t talking about the marines)
@bear_fam4 is taking the L1 today at @crossfitranch. He lost 100 lbs in 1 year. And now is excited to become a CFL1 trainer and help others. @crossfittraining #crossfit #crossfittraining

8:34am. Big L1 staff for this mornings MDL1 at CrossFit HQ. @katiehogan777 @juliefoucher @patbarbercf @hollismolloy @joewesterlin @zac.pine @wespiatt2013 @crossfittraining @nicole.carroll #crossfit #crossfittraining #crossfitseminarstaff

7:20am
Did crossfit.com workout from a few days ago. 20 minutes 5 strict chest to bar pull-up 10 ring pushups 20 30” box step ups. This was a slow yet hard workout. Pushups were thumb to chest. First time doing ring pushups in years. This set was towards the end. I got 6 rounds plus some step ups. @dougthedogo constantly providing a nice push. @crossfittraining #crossfit #wod #crossfitwod #dogoargentino

7:22am
5 rounds of run 400 3 bar muscle-ups. The muscle-ups were easy so on final round decided to go for a bigger set, as seen here. @dougthedogo did the runs with me. #crossfit #crossfittraining @crossfittraining #dogoargentino @newworlddogo
My Direct messages can get interesting...@jorwatches @miche_lino_stas @gmo_2012. @tdchunts

8:30am
I like to warm up with speed bag work to get the blood flowing and upper body warm. I also just like the bag so that makes it a enjoyable part of the process. Sometimes I will do workouts with the speed bag, but not often. One that I do when I am short on time is ‘5 rounds of 1 minute of burpees 1 minute of speed bag.’ I didn’t do that today. @dougthedogo @crossfit @crossfittraining #crossfit #crossfittraining #dogoargentino

Programmed by @streetparking.  Masters 40+ version. 
80dbl - 40 35lb dbsnatch - 20 pull-ups 
60-30-15. 40-20-10. 9:37. All sets unbroken.

#Repost @dougthedogo with @get_repost
・・・
@barbellsforbullies is hosting an online Competition to support their program pairing rescued and trained pit bulls as service dogs with veterans suffering from PTSD.  They asked if I would do it and Doug thought we should. This is the first event. The competition consists of two online workouts. They are programmed by @streetparking.  I did the masters 40+ version of event 1 and finished the round of 10 cleans. Looking forward to number two and supporting a good cause. Sign up at 
https://www.barbellsforbullies.org/sitrep #crossfit #dogoargentino

Big win for us against an organization that chose to lie about us. Check out www.crossfit.com for full story... @nscaofficial “On Dec. 4, 2019, Judge Janis L. Sammartino ordered terminating sanctions against the National Strength and Conditioning Association (NSCA) in the case of CrossFit, Inc. v. NSCA. With this ruling, the court ordered the NSCA to pay CrossFit, Inc. $3,997,868.66 as a sanction and then terminated the case in CrossFit’s favor. The Court also awarded numerous issue sanctions that conclude the NSCA’s corrupt practices harmed CrossFit (while benefiting the NSCA) in the military, U.S., and international communities.

CrossFit, Inc. sued the NSCA after the NSCA published a “scientific” study containing false and fabricated data about CrossFit’s injury rate that was designed specifically to harm CrossFit’s business and reputation. Additionally, as elaborated in CrossFit, Inc.’s June 2019 request for terminating sanctions:......” Congrats to Greg, @marshall.brenner and all those in HQ who fought this battle. #crossfit #nsca @crossfittraining #crossfittraining

9:34am
10 rounds of 10 airsquats and 10 kb pushpress.  It’s raining hard in California. #crossfit @crossfittraining

#Repost @tdchunts with @get_repost
・・・
Team unknown distance competition today at @avenaltactical.  My partner @9_dolls and I took the win.  Fun match set up by @woodhouse.scott and Jim. @masterpiecearms @leupoldoptics @federalpremium

11:35am
20.5 scaled. 
Did it chipper style. Pull-ups then wallball then row. 
I had planned on doing 20 pull-ups but once I hit that point they felt fine so I decided to try for 40 unbroken.  It’s been years since I have done that. (Some of these look low, but it’s just the camera angle.). The wall balls were a mess because of my wall ball set up. And the row was just steady.  This scaled version would also be a good workout in a CF affiliate.  @crossfittraining #crossfit #crossfittraining #crossfitgames

10:20am
20.4 scaled. Harder than I expected. Step ups with Med ball are slow. I didn’t finish. Give it a try. #crossfit #crossfittraining #crossfitgames @crossfittraining

9:45am
4 mile run with 50lb pack. 37:21. 9:25 mile pace. Felt good. Don’t think we will need to keep a pace like this at @mammothsniperchallenge in January. But just in case.  Pack by @hyperlite_mountain_gear  With some small mods. #mammothsniperchallenge @dagofl @leupoldoptics @federalpremium @masterpiecearms @crossfitranch #crossfit
Repping our teams. #finsup

20.3 scaled.  I forgot how bad hand release pushups can be. And bear crawling is not fun. Finished under the cap but wasted 1 minute going after @dougthedogo. #crossfit #crossfittraining @crossfittraining

Once the open ended I decided that my next 5 workouts would be the scaled version of them in the order they appeared.  Yesterday I did 20.1 scaled. Today 20.2 scaled.  I got 23 +1 today. Even scaled these still burn. #crossfit #crossfitgames @crossfittraining
